picasasync is a simple utility that allows you sync local directories
containing digital photos to your picasa albums in the cloud.


usage: picasasync.py [-h] [-d] [-v] local remote

Sync directories with picasa

positional arguments:
  local          Local directory you'd like to sync
  remote         Remote album to which you'd like to sync

optional arguments:
  -h, --help     show this help message and exit
  -d, --dry-run  Only print what we would sync, don't actually sync
  -v, --verbose  Be verbose

by Mitchel Humpherys <mitch.special@gmail.com>
